The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, specifically the problem of finding stable sets that hit maximum and maximal cliques in a graph. This falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also involves the study of graph coloring and the relationship between cliques and stable sets, which are topics in graph theory (cs.GT) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper presents a counterexample to a recent conjecture, which is a result in theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
